stories.text:
Currently my extended family (~25 people) have a shared WhatsApp group in which we share milestones or any things deemed worthy. I am hoping to find a better way of keeping up to date, as the chat is very quiet. I hesitate to start posting regularly as I know others don't and it may dominate the conversation.

Clearly 25 is too many to have on video or phone call, as well as to speak individually on a regular basis. How does everyone keep up?
stories.title: Ask HN: How do you socialise with your extended family online?
